g.text: Attaining the durability of high-efﬁciency perovskite solar cells (PSCs) operated under concomitant
light and thermal stresses is still a serious concern before large-scale application. It is crucial to
maintain the phase stability of the organic hole-transporting layer for thermostable PSCs across
a range of temperatures sampled during device operation. To address this issue, we propose a
racemic semiconducting glassy ﬁlm with remarkable morphological stability, exempliﬁed here by
a low-molecular symmetry oxa[5]helicene-centered organic semiconductor (O5H-OMeDPA). The he-
